{
  "texts": [
    "To highlight different clusters, we employ our spacing strategy on clusters instead of nodes.",
    "Given a space-filling curve of a specific order, we first calculate the length of the curve L, the total amount of space available for the nodes, and L -N, the amount of space to be redistributed, where N is the size of the hypergraph.",
    "Our goal is to distribute the space between clusters to ensure the best readability.",
    "In early prototyping, we found that distributing the space proportional to the cluster size gives the best readability as well as stability.",
    "Specifically, we define the space of a cluster as the blank space it has behind it on the curve, which is calculated by (L -N) Nc N, where N c is the size of the cluster (Figure4)."
  ]
}